<br>
Its Myst's first time.  We know better so we ask her/him to try zoning in first.  S/he couldn't.  (I had problem the first time, no big deal, just need to get it fixed.)  So we go through the typical diagnostics:<br>
<br>
- did you download the files?<br>
- did you check the download box in the patcher?<br>
- why don't you try exit out, deleting all the mm* files (mistmoore) and repatch, join us when you're done?<br>
<br>
Then this tard starts throwing a tantrum, yelling s/he is not a clueless retard, left group, gated back to PoK.  Geesh, what are you? 5 years old?  LDoN had been out for 3 weeks.  If you can't zone in, you have a problem with your system or account.  We are trying to help you get it fixed and you threw a freaking tantrum like a child?!  <br>
<br>
Ok fine, we have a pally tank and a necro mezzer, we can deal with undeads.  Zone in.  Then her guildie Korey (mage) LD and never came back.  Geesh, thanks for nothing.<br>
<br>
This was going to be a Peritus rant (both Mystleto and Korey are Peritus), <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>BUT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 2 of the people (actually one, the other is a bot) left in the group are Peritus also. I'm glad he had the integrity to stick around.  We still had a good time doing a 4-people crawl and experienced some excellent team work.<br>
<br>
Screwing others is one thing but screwing your own guildies?  That just tells me there is absolutely no integrity behind the keyboard.  Just a child.  <br>
<br>
Here's my advice to you: Quit the damn game and go back and play your Gameboy in your little corner by yourself.  You have no business in an MMOG.<br>
<br>
My advice to y'all:  Ignore this tard or you'll get screwed.<br>
<br>
My advice to Peritus:  I know Myst is a trial member, kick him/her out.  You don't need people who would screw their own guildies.  No guild does.<br>
<br>
